mappings.name: Submits a sitemap for a site. - 200
Retrieves information about a specific sitemap.

schema.description: Contains detailed information about a specific URL submitted as a [sitemap](https://support.google.com/webmasters/answer/156184).

contents.description: The various content types in the sitemap.

errors.description: Number of errors in the sitemap. These are issues with the sitemap itself that need to be fixed before it can be processed correctly.

isPending.description: If true, the sitemap has not been processed.

isSitemapsIndex.description: If true, the sitemap is a collection of sitemaps.

lastDownloaded.description: Date & time in which this sitemap was last downloaded. Date format is in RFC 3339 format (yyyy-mm-dd).

lastSubmitted.description: Date & time in which this sitemap was submitted. Date format is in RFC 3339 format (yyyy-mm-dd).

type.description: The type of the sitemap. For example: `rssFeed`.

warnings.description: Number of warnings for the sitemap. These are generally non-critical issues with URLs in the sitemaps.

sitemap.description: Contains detailed information about a specific URL submitted as a [sitemap](https://support.google.com/webmasters/answer/156184).

mappings.name: Query your data with filters and parameters that you define. Returns zero or mor...

schema.description: A list of rows, one per result, grouped by key. Metrics in each row are aggregated for all data grouped by that key either by page or property, as specified by the aggregation type parameter.

rows.description: A list of rows grouped by the key values in the order given in the query.

mappings.name: Adds a site to the set of the user's sites in Search Console. - 200

schema.description: Contains permission level information about a Search Console site. For more information, see [Permissions in Search Console](https://support.google.com/webmasters/answer/2451999).

permissionLevel.description: The user's permission level for the site.

mappings.name: Removes a site from the set of the user's Search Console sites. - 200
Lists the user's Search Console sites.

schema.description: List of sites with access level information.

siteEntry.description: Contains permission level information about a Search Console site. For more information, see [Permissions in Search Console](https://support.google.com/webmasters/answer/2451999).

mappings.name: Runs Mobile-Friendly Test for a given URL.

schema.description: Mobile-friendly test response, including mobile-friendly issues and resource issues.

mobileFriendliness.description: Test verdict, whether the page is mobile friendly or not.
